stylometry: The variables that you must consider when setting he level of saftey stock is, number one the demand. It is hard to predict the demand of a certain product becasue the market is always changing but you dont want to run into the problem of having to much saftey stock because then you will end up loosing money on that inventory you are setting aside. Another variable you have to consider is holding costs. It costs money to have inventory just sitting in the back shelves of your company and it can also get broken or stolen being back there, this could loose you money as well. Another variable you have to consider when setting the level of saftey stock is ordering costs.
